ZH: 我睡眼惺忪地看了一眼闹钟。
EN: I groggily glanced at the alarm clock with bleary eyes.

ZH: 她睡眼惺忪地走进厨房，准备早餐。
EN: She shuffled into the kitchen with bleary eyes, preparing breakfast.

ZH: 他看起来睡眼惺忪，一定是昨晚熬夜了。
EN: He looks bleary-eyed, he must have stayed up late last night.

ZH: 早上起床时，我总是睡眼惺忪。
EN: I always wake up bleary-eyed in the morning.

ZH: 昨晚只睡了几个小时，他早上起床时睡眼惺忪。
EN: He only slept a few hours last night, so he woke up bleary-eyed in the morning.

ZH: 她的睡眼惺忪的样子很可爱。
EN: Her bleary-eyed look is so adorable.

ZH: 他睡眼惺忪地回答了问题。
EN: He answered the question with bleary eyes.

ZH: 被闹钟吵醒后，她睡眼惺忪地起床了。
EN: She groggily got out of bed with bleary eyes after being woken up by the alarm clock.

ZH: 他睡眼惺忪地走进办公室，希望别人不要打扰他。
EN: He walked into the office with bleary eyes, hoping no one would disturb him.

ZH: 长途旅行后，我睡眼惺忪地回到家。
EN: After a long journey, I returned home with bleary eyes.

ZH: 昨晚开了个派对，今天早上他们都睡眼惺忪。
EN: They all had bleary eyes this morning after throwing a party last night.

ZH: 起床前，她总是睡眼惺忪。
EN: She always has bleary eyes before getting out of bed.

ZH: 他睡眼惺忪地走到厨房里倒了一杯咖啡。
EN: He groggily walked into the kitchen and poured himself a cup of coffee with bleary eyes.

ZH: 待了一整夜的机场后，我睡眼惺忪地登上飞机。
EN: After spending the whole night at the airport, I boarded the plane with bleary eyes.

ZH: 她睡眼惺忪地翻了个身，又继续睡了。
EN: She rolled over with bleary eyes and went back to sleep.

ZH: 起床时，他总是睡眼惺忪的，需要喝咖啡提神。
EN: He always wakes up bleary-eyed in the morning and needs coffee to wake up.

ZH: 对于不爱早起的人来说，每天早上都是睡眼惺忪的状态。
EN: For those who don't like getting up early, every morning is a bleary-eyed state.

ZH: 在开会时，他睡眼惺忪地听着报告。
EN: He listened to the presentation with bleary eyes during the meeting.

ZH: 每当我睡眼惺忪的时候，我就想起了妈妈的话：“早睡早起身体好”。
EN: Whenever I am bleary-eyed, I remember my mother's words: "Early to bed, early to rise, makes a man healthy, wealthy, and wise."

ZH: 起床后，她一脸睡眼惺忪地准备去上班。
EN: She prepared to go to work with a bleary-eyed look after getting out of bed.
